---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StepCard from '../../components/StepCard.astro';
---

<Layout title="Install OpenClaw on Windows" lang="en" currentPath="/guide/install-windows" description="Install OpenClaw on Windows 10 or 11 using WSL2, Ubuntu, and Node.js.">
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="badge badge-cyan">Windows Install Guide</span>
      <h1>Install on Windows</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">OpenClaw runs on Windows 10 and 11 via WSL2 (Windows Subsystem for Linux). This gives you a full Ubuntu environment without dual-booting.</p>
      <div class="lang-notice">
        <a href="/zh/guide/install-windows">üáπüáº Èñ±ËÆÄ‰∏≠ÊñáÁâà</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <aside class="toc">
          <div class="toc-inner">
            <div class="toc-title">On This Page</div>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#requirements">Requirements</a></li>
              <li><a href="#wsl2">Install WSL2</a></li>
              <li><a href="#ubuntu">Set Up Ubuntu</a></li>
              <li><a href="#nodejs">Install Node.js</a></li>
              <li><a href="#openclaw">Install OpenClaw</a></li>
              <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <article class="article">
          <section id="requirements" class="article-section">
            <h2>Requirements</h2>
            <div class="requirements-grid">
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">ü™ü</div>
                <div class="req-label">Windows</div>
                <div class="req-value">10 (21H2+) or 11</div>
                <div class="req-note">WSL2 requires 64-bit Windows</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üêß</div>
                <div class="req-label">WSL2</div>
                <div class="req-value">Ubuntu 22.04 LTS</div>
                <div class="req-note">Free from Microsoft Store</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üü¢</div>
                <div class="req-label">Node.js</div>
                <div class="req-value">v22 or later</div>
                <div class="req-note">Installed inside WSL2</div>
              </div>
              <div class="req-card">
                <div class="req-icon">üîë</div>
                <div class="req-label">API Key</div>
                <div class="req-value">Anthropic recommended</div>
                <div class="req-note">Get one at console.anthropic.com</div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-icon">‚ÑπÔ∏è</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Why WSL2?</strong> OpenClaw uses Unix-native features (daemon management, file sockets) that require a Linux environment.
                WSL2 provides a full Linux kernel running inside Windows with near-native performance. Once set up, you'll barely notice it's there.
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="wsl2" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 1: Install WSL2</h2>
            <p>
              We're going to build a small room inside Windows (called WSL2) specifically for running your AI. This keeps everything stable and won't break anything on your existing computer. The whole process is automatic ‚Äî you just copy and paste a few commands.
            </p>

            <div class="info-box">
              <span class="info-icon">üí°</span>
              <div>
                <strong>Don't be scared of the blue window!</strong> PowerShell is Windows' built-in command input window ‚Äî it's like typing instructions for your computer to follow. It won't break anything.
              </div>
            </div>

            <p>
              Open <strong>PowerShell as Administrator</strong> (right-click Start ‚Üí "Windows PowerShell (Admin)" or "Terminal (Admin)") and run:
            </p>
            <pre><code>wsl --install</code></pre>

            <div class="terminal-preview">
              <div class="terminal-bar">
                <span class="dot dot-blue"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">Administrator: Windows PowerShell</span>
              </div>
              <pre class="terminal-body"><code><span class="t-prompt">PS C:\Windows\System32></span> wsl --install
Installing: Windows Subsystem for Linux
Windows Subsystem for Linux has been installed.
Installing: Ubuntu
Ubuntu has been installed.
The requested operation is successful.
Changes will not be effective until the system is restarted.</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p>
              This command installs WSL2 with Ubuntu by default. <strong>Restart your computer</strong> when prompted.
            </p>

            <div class="tip-box">
              <strong>üìö Official Microsoft Docs:</strong> For detailed WSL2 setup options, see
              <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/wsl/install" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
                Microsoft's official WSL installation guide
              </a>.
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="ubuntu" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 2: Set Up Ubuntu</h2>
            <p>After restarting, Ubuntu will open automatically and finish setting up. You'll be asked to create a username and password:</p>

            <div class="terminal-preview">
              <div class="terminal-bar">
                <span class="dot dot-blue"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">Ubuntu on Windows</span>
              </div>
              <pre class="terminal-body"><code>Enter new UNIX username: <span class="t-input">yourname</span>
New password: <span class="t-input">‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢</span>
Retype new password: <span class="t-input">‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢‚Ä¢</span>
passwd: password updated successfully

Welcome to Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS (GNU/Linux 5.15.0-1 x86_64)
yourname@DESKTOP-XXXXX:~$</code></pre>
            </div>

            <p>Update the system packages first:</p>
            <pre><code>sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y</code></pre>

            <p>To open Ubuntu again later, search for "Ubuntu" in Start, or type <code>wsl</code> in any terminal.</p>
          </section>

          <section id="nodejs" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 3: Install Node.js</h2>
            <p>Install Node.js 22 inside Ubuntu using the NodeSource repository:</p>
            <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_22.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt-get install -y nodejs</code></pre>

            <p>Verify the installation:</p>
            <pre><code>node --version   # v22.x.x
npm --version    # 10.x.x</code></pre>

            <div class="terminal-preview">
              <div class="terminal-bar">
                <span class="dot dot-blue"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">Ubuntu on Windows</span>
              </div>
              <pre class="terminal-body"><code><span class="t-prompt">$</span> node --version
v22.14.0
<span class="t-prompt">$</span> npm --version
10.9.2</code></pre>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="openclaw" class="article-section">
            <h2>Step 4: Install & Run OpenClaw</h2>

            <StepCard number={1} title="Install OpenClaw globally">
              <pre><code>npm install -g openclaw@latest</code></pre>
              <p>Verify:</p>
              <pre><code>openclaw --version</code></pre>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={2} title="Run the onboarding wizard">
              <pre><code>openclaw onboard --install-daemon</code></pre>
              <p>Follow the prompts to enter your API KeyÔºàAI ÁöÑÂ∏≥ËôüÈë∞ÂåôÔºåÂ∞±ÂÉèÂØÜÁ¢º‰∏ÄÊ®£Ôºâand configure your workspace. The background auto-start service installs inside WSL2.</p>
              <div class="tip-box">
                <strong>üí° Note:</strong> The WSL2 background service starts automatically when you open WSL. For fully persistent 24/7 uptime without keeping WSL open, consider a <a href="/guide/install-vps">VPS installation</a> instead.
              </div>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={3} title="Start the Gateway">
              <pre><code>openclaw gateway --port 18789</code></pre>
              <p>Open <a href="http://127.0.0.1:18789" target="_blank">http://127.0.0.1:18789</a> in your Windows browser to see the Control UI ‚Äî WSL2 networking is shared with Windows automatically.</p>
              <div class="success-box">
                <strong>‚úÖ It works!</strong> You can now connect Telegram, WhatsApp, or Discord.
              </div>
              <div class="warning-box">
                <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Important:</strong> If you shut down your computer or close the Ubuntu window, your AI will temporarily stop responding to messages. If you want your AI online 24/7, we recommend switching to a <a href="/guide/install-vps">VPS installation</a> instead.
              </div>
            </StepCard>

            <StepCard number={4} title="Connect Telegram">
              <pre><code>openclaw channels login</code></pre>
              <p>Follow the <a href="/guide/telegram">Telegram guide</a> to connect your bot in under 5 minutes.</p>
            </StepCard>
          </section>

          <section id="faq" class="article-section">
            <h2>FAQ</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Does WSL2 work on Windows 10?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>Yes, WSL2 works on Windows 10 version 21H2 (October 2021 Update) or later. Run <code>winver</code> to check your version. If you're below 21H2, run Windows Update first.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  Will OpenClaw keep running if I close the Ubuntu window?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>WSL2 continues running in the background even when you close the terminal window. The background service stays active. However, WSL2 may be shut down by Windows after ~8 seconds of no active sessions. For truly 24/7 uptime, a VPS is recommended. See our <a href="/guide/install-vps">VPS guide</a>.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
                  How do I access my Windows files from WSL2?
                  <span class="faq-arrow">‚ñº</span>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-a">
                  <p>Your Windows drives are mounted at <code>/mnt/c/</code>, <code>/mnt/d/</code>, etc. inside WSL2. However, it's best to store your OpenClaw workspace inside the Linux filesystem (<code>~/</code>) for better performance.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="support-note">
              Having trouble? Join the <a href="https://discord.com/invite/clawd" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OpenClaw Discord community</a> or <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">report an issue</a>.
            </div>
          </section>

          <div class="nav-buttons">
            <a href="/guide/install" class="btn btn-outline">‚Üê Choose Platform</a>
            <a href="/guide/telegram" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Connect Telegram ‚Üí</a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(0,212,255,0.07) 0%, transparent 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero .badge { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lang-notice { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .lang-notice a { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

  .page-content { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 3rem; align-items: start; }

  .toc-inner { position: sticky; top: 84px; background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.25rem; }
  .toc-title { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text2); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .toc ul { list-style: none; }
  .toc li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .toc a { color: var(--text2); font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .toc a:hover { color: var(--accent); opacity: 1; }

  .article-section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }
  .article-section h2 { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; padding-bottom: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .article-section p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; }
  .article-section ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0.75rem 0 1rem; }
  .article-section ul li { padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text2); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .article-section ul li::before { content: "‚Üí"; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--accent); }
  .article-section pre { margin: 1rem 0; }

  .requirements-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .req-card { background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.25rem; text-align: center; }
  .req-icon { font-size: 1.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .req-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--text2); margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .req-value { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .req-note { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text2); }

  .info-box, .tip-box, .success-box { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius); margin: 1.25rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .info-box { background: rgba(0,212,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(0,212,255,0.2); color: var(--text2); }
  .info-icon { font-size: 1.1rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 0.1rem; }
  .tip-box { background: rgba(255,107,53,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,107,53,0.2); color: var(--text2); }
  .success-box { background: rgba(0,200,100,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(0,200,100,0.2); color: var(--text2); }

  .terminal-preview { background: #0d1117; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden; margin: 1.25rem 0; }
  .terminal-bar { background: #161b22; padding: 0.6rem 1rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #30363d; }
  .dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .dot-red { background: #ff5f57; }
  .dot-yellow { background: #febc2e; }
  .dot-green { background: #28c840; }
  .dot-blue { background: #007acc; width: 14px; height: 14px; }
  .terminal-title { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #8b949e; margin-left: 0.5rem; font-family: var(--mono); }
  .terminal-body { background: #0d1117; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin: 0; border: none; border-radius: 0; font-size: 0.83rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .terminal-body code { background: none; color: #e6edf3; padding: 0; }
  .t-prompt { color: #58a6ff; }
  .t-input { color: #3fb950; }

  .warning-box { background: rgba(255,200,0,0.07); border: 1px solid rgba(255,200,0,0.3); color: var(--text2); display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius); margin: 1.25rem 0; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .support-note { margin-top: 1.5rem; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text2); }
  .support-note a { color: var(--accent); }
  .faq-list { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .nav-buttons { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 1rem; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .toc { display: none; }
    .requirements-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .requirements-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .nav-buttons { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  }
</style>
